        {"id":"prjevtxt","elType":"column","settings":{"_column_size":50,"content_position":"middle"},"elements":[
          {"id":"prjevlbl","elType":"widget","widgetType":"text-editor","settings":{"editor":"<p><span style=\"display:inline-block;font-size:.75rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0056A0;background:#e8f2fc;padding:4px 14px;border-radius:20px;\">E-Mobility</span></p>"},"elements":[]},
          {"id":"prjevhdg","elType":"widget","widgetType":"heading","settings":{"title":"EV Conversion","header_size":"h2","title_color":"#0056A0","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":24,"sizes":[]},"typography_font_weight":"700"},"elements":[]},
          {"id":"prjevdesc","elType":"widget","widgetType":"text-editor","settings":{"editor":"<p>We specialize in the conversion of Class 5 and 8 trucks from diesel to electric using cutting-edge e-axle technology. Our EV conversion services help reduce diesel consumption and pollution while significantly increasing travel range, up to 1,300 miles. Our notable clients include: Staples, UPS, FedEx, Kenworth etc.</p><p style=\"margin-top:14px;\"><strong>Long-Term Operational Benefits:</strong> Evaluating the financial and environmental benefits of hydrogen trucks and EV conversions, including cost savings, reduced maintenance expenses, and improved sustainability.</p>"},"elements":[]}
        ]}
      ]
    },

    {
      "id": "prjlng01",
      "elType": "section",
      "settings": {"background_background":"classic","background_color":"#f7f9fc","padding":{"unit":"px","top":"96","right":"0","bottom":"96","left":"0","isLinked":false},"gap":"extended"},
      "elements": [
        {"id":"prjlngtxt","elType":"column","settings":{"_column_size":50,"content_position":"middle"},"elements":[
          {"id":"prjlnglbl","elType":"widget","widgetType":"text-editor","settings":{"editor":"<p><span style=\"display:inline-block;font-size:.75rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0056A0;background:#e8f2fc;padding:4px 14px;border-radius:20px;\">LNG & LPG</span></p>"},"elements":[]},
          {"id":"prjlnghdg","elType":"widget","widgetType":"heading","settings":{"title":"LNG & LPG Infrastructure and Logistics","header_size":"h2","title_color":"#0056A0","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":24,"sizes":[]},"typography_font_weight":"700"},"elements":[]},
          {"id":"prjlngdesc","elType":"widget","widgetType":"text-editor","settings":{"editor":"<p>Amerigroup is a trusted partner in clean fuel mobility, energy transition logistics, and regasification infrastructure across the Americas and beyond. Our long-standing presence in U.S. – Mexico LNG and LPG corridors provides the foundation for scalable, reliable energy solutions:</p><p style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:.9rem;color:#555c6b;\"><strong style=\"color:#1a1a2e;\">LNG and LPG Transportation:</strong> End-to-end transport solutions by ship, truck, ISO container, and pipeline, ensuring secure delivery across borders</p><p style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:.9rem;color:#555c6b;\"><strong style=\"color:#1a1a2e;\">Onshore Regasification:</strong> Localized conversion of LNG back to natural gas for utilities, factories, and power grids</p><p style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:.9rem;color:#555c6b;\"><strong style=\"color:#1a1a2e;\">FSRU:</strong> Rapid-deployment offshore terminals that provide LNG import and regas capacity without the need for land-based infrastructure</p><p style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:.9rem;color:#555c6b;\"><strong style=\"color:#1a1a2e;\">Marine Bunkering:</strong> Supplying LNG as a cleaner fuel for maritime fleets</p><p style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:.9rem;color:#555c6b;\"><strong style=\"color:#1a1a2e;\">Comprehensive LNG Chain Management:</strong> From export and storage to regasification and dispatch, we offer full-scope LNG handling</p><p style=\"margin-top:10px;font-size:.9rem;color:#555c6b;\"><strong style=\"color:#1a1a2e;\">Small-Scale Distribution:</strong> Delivering LNG and LPG to off-grid, rural, or remote industrial sites</p><p style=\"margin-top:20px;padding:16px;background:#e8f2fc;border-radius:8px;font-size:.88rem;font-style:italic;color:#003d73;\">The U.S. Department of Energy (DOE) has approved AmerigroupLNG to export approximately 4.6 billion cubic feet (Bcf) of liquefied natural gas (LNG) from the United States. This significant achievement underscores our commitment to providing high-quality energy solutions and expanding our global reach.</p>"},"elements":[]}
        ]},
        {"id":"prjlngimg","elType":"column","settings":{"_column_size":50},"elements":[
